            <div type="intro">
                <p>Introduction to the Encomium to Seng’an Daoyi</p>
                <p>This text, like HDS 18, “Encomium to Fahong,” is not included in any traditional
                    collection. In addition, the two texts might be seen as constituting a separate
                    genre of monastic encomium, one which resembles traditional biographical genres
                    only on the surface. The first sentence of the present text, according to the
                    conventions of Chinese literature, marks it as biography. Yet what follows is
                    more a panegyric to Fahong’s talents and spiritual majesty more than a biography
                    in the usual sense.</p>
            </div>
            <div xml:lang="en">
                <div>
                    <p> The great śramaṇa <persName corresp="zh-a1" key="rh0004" type="monk" xml:id="en-a1">
                            <addName corresp="zh-a2" type="clerical" xml:id="en-a2">Seng’an</addName>
                        </persName>, also named <persName corresp="zh-a3" key="rh0004" type="monk" xml:id="en-a3">
                            <addName corresp="zh-a4" type="clerical" xml:id="en-a4">Daoyi</addName>
                        </persName>, is a man of the neighborhood of Empty Immensity within the
                        village of Vast Enormity. He is quiescent [ . . . ] [within] the Three Times
                            <ptr target="note_en_1"/>, like the thousand peaks of <placeName corresp="zh-a5" key="dh0003" type="mountain" xml:id="en-a5">Amassed
                            Stones</placeName>. <ptr target="note_en_2"/>Sire’s substance is massive
                        and colossal, like the myriad summits of <placeName corresp="zh-a6" key="d02190" type="mountain" xml:id="en-a6">Empty
                        Undividedness</placeName>. <ptr target="note_en_3"/> How majestic is his
                        virtue! How unfettered is his genius! </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <ab>Thus we make a verse saying:</ab>
                    <lg>
                        <l>He piles up jades and jewels,</l>
                        <l>[Day after] day he polishes the principle. <ptr target="note_en_4"/>
                        </l>
                        <l>On stone after stone he chisels and engraves</l>
                        <l>On mountain after mountain he [ . . . ] [ . . . ]</l>
                    </lg>
                </div>
                <dateline>
                    <dateStruct calendar="Buddhist" corresp="zh-a7" xml:id="en-a7">One thousand six
                        hundred [ ... ] [ ... ] years after the twin trees</dateStruct>
                </dateline>
            </div>
